  "doc_id": "33198",
  "text": "With all three methods, there was a major decrease in the percentage of true retention (%TR) after the drying, suggesting that combinations of exposure to air and heat will severely affect the β-carotene retention. Even though concentration levels were higher in some varieties than in the fresh roots, the increase may be the result of the reduction of moisture and solid losses that increase the carotene per unit weight of the intermediate products. This observation is consistent with other literature [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , where processing resulted in higher carotenoid content per unit weight.",
